  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Rapidly acting emetic agent\nDerived from the ipecacuanha plant\nOften abused by adults with eating disorders\nOccasionally seen used in Munchausen by proxy",
      "subsections": {
        "Mechanism_of_Action": {
          "text": "Vomiting\nImmediate: direct irritation of gastric mucosa\nDelayed: absorption, stimulation of chemoreceptor trigger zone\nInhibition of protein synthesis in skeletal muscle",
          "tables": []
        },
        "Toxic_Dose": {
          "text": "Acute\nAs little as 10 mL of the potent fluid extract can cause death\n120 mL of syrup of ipecac unlikely to cause severe toxicity\nChronic\nSlow elimination of emetine causes cumulative toxicity\nDaily ingestion of 90-120 mL of syrup for several months can cause cardiomyopathy and death",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
